Definition:  CFORMAT_NAME(name)

Description: Displays a player name in an 11 space field with justification
             to the left to make it easier to print in tables. The name is
	     capitalized.

Arguments  : string name - the name of the player.

Returns    : string - the capitalized name of the player with spaces padded.

Example    : CFORMAT_NAME("foobar") -> "Foobar     "

See also   : FORMAT_NAME
